  "text": "The presumed plume at Yellowstone seems to have variable influence on the crustal velocities, such that some volcanoes are underlain by low-velocity bodies and other areas are underlain by high-velocity zones in the lower crust [CITATION_1] . The low velocities may be explained by high temperature below the presently active volcanoes, whereas the high velocities potentially could be caused by magmatic bodies of underplated type, but seismic observations indicate that underplating may not be a dominant process at Yellowstone.",
